The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 01 December is 9,177 (1,062.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 26 November, there were 552 new confirmed cases (63.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 19 November, there were 948 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 42% (396 fewer cases).
